Bruegel: Sermon of St. John: from Bergheim in Alsace, cf. Predella by the Master of Stauffenberg Altar with the Sermon of St. John in Kolmar [sic] Unterlinden (Alfred Stange, Deutsche Malerei der Gotik, VII [Oberrhein, Bodensee, Schweiz und Mittelrhein in der Zeit von 1450 bis 1500, Berlin: Deutscher Kunstverlag], 1955, Abb. 20. The traditional representation (cf. also Bouts) St. John (with 2 apostles and with a crowd of people sitting before him pointing to Christ with his right hand (Christ on the right) with the words ecce agnus dei [sic] is seeing from his mouth.
